    <div class="faq-section-2 is-hidden">
     <div class="faq-container">
      <div class="title-wrap-3">
       <h3 class="h3 is-services-page">
        Frequently Asked Questions about Teeth Whitening
       </h3>
       <p class="paragraph-large">
        This is where all the answers to your teeth whitening questions are.
       </p>
      </div>
      <div class="w-layout-grid faq-grid-3">
       <div class="faq-wrap-2">
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           Is teeth whitening painful?
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           No, teeth whitening is not painful. However, some people may experience temporary side effects, such as increased sensitivity of the teeth and gums. If you have sensitive teeth or gums, be sure to talk to your dentist before undergoing teeth whitening.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           What are the risks of teeth whitening?
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           The most common side effect of teeth whitening is increased tooth and gum sensitivity. This usually goes away within a few days after the procedure. In rare cases, people may experience more serious side effects, such as burns to the gums or throat, from using bleaching products. Be sure to follow the instructions on any over-the-counter teeth whitening products you use and talk to your dentist if you experience any side effects.
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           What are the benefits of teeth whitening?
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           Teeth whitening can boost your self-confidence and make you feel better about your appearance. It can also be used to improve the look of your teeth before getting braces or other dental work.
           <a class="link" href="san-francisco-dental-studio.php">
            Talk to one of our dentists
           </a>
           about whether teeth whitening is right for you.
           <br/>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           How long does teeth whitening last?
           <br/>
           <br/>
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           Teeth whitening is not permanent. You may need to repeat the procedure every few years to maintain the desired level of whiteness. Some over-the-counter teeth whitening products claim to have long-lasting results, but these claims have not been proven. Talk to your dentist about how often you should repeat the procedure.
           <br/>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           How does teeth whitening occur?
           <br/>
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           Teeth whitening occurs in two ways, either by
           <strong class="bold-text">
            bleaching
           </strong>
           or
           <strong class="bold-text">
            mechanically
           </strong>
           .
           <br/>
           The most common approach to teeth whitening is bleaching. This can be done at home using over-the-counter products or in a dentist's office. The active ingredient in these bleaching products is usually hydrogen peroxide or carbamide peroxide, which breaks down into hydrogen peroxide.
           <br/>
           The second way to achieve teeth whitening is through mechanical means. This generally occurs in a dentist's office and involves using abrasives to remove surface stains from the teeth. Abrasive materials include silica, aluminum oxide, calcium carbonate, and baking soda. Mechanical tooth whitening can also be achieved by using a power brush with special bristles or getting your teeth professionally cleaned.
           <br/>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-question-wrap">
         <a class="faq-question-bar-3 w-inline-block" href="#">
          <h3 class="h3 question-title-4">
           What can you do to avoid teeth stains?
           <br/>
          </h3>
          <img alt="Blue Plus logo " class="image-9" src="./resources/cdn.prod.website-files.com/6230bfc886c8142108c44052/6230bfc886c8148790c440ce_close-fill.svg"/>
         </a>
         <div class="faq-content-4">
          <p class="faq-paragraph-4">
           There are a few things you can do at home to help keep your teeth looking their best and prevent staining in the first place.
           <br/>
           ‍
           <br/>
           -Quit smoking: Smoking is one of the leading causes of teeth staining. If you smoke, quitting is the best thing you can do for your teeth.
           <br/>
           -Brush and floss regularly: Brushing and flossing helps remove plaque, which can cause teeth staining. Be sure to brush twice a day for two minutes each time and floss daily.
           <br/>
           -Limit teeth-staining foods and drinks: Coffee, tea, red wine, and dark berries can all cause teeth staining. If you consume these products, be sure to brush
           <br/>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
